Stephen Turnbull



Stephen Turnbull is Director of Marketing for AMD’s embedded business within the Enterprise Solutions Business Unit. He is responsible for delivering “whole product” solutions for focused embedded vertical markets and driving go-to-market strategy.
Turnbull has been with AMD for 2 years in the Embedded Solutions Business Unit. Initially he was responsible for the Thin Client vertical where he secured double digit market share grown and cemented AMD’s number 1 position in the market. He has subsequently taken on a wider role with responsibility for all AMD’s focused embedded vertical markets including, thin clients, casino gaming, digital signage, industrial and medical imaging.
Prior to joining AMD Turnbull worked for Motorola Semiconductor and more recently for Freescale Semiconductor where his most recent position was Director of Marketing for Wireless Infrastructure. In a career spanning over 30 years he has worked across almost every semiconductor market segment including networking, industrial, computer, consumer and automotive. In each case he has engaged a customer base of leading blue chip corporations to deliver profitable growth and leadership market positions.
Originally a native of Scotland, Turnbull is now based in Austin, Texas where he lives with his wife Philippa and their two children Blair & Mhairi. Turnbull holds a B.Sc. in Electrical Engineering & Marketing from Strathclyde University and a Masters in Corporate Leadership from Napier University. He is an enthusiastic rugby supporter and a keen golfer.









